Job Description
A leading Oil and Gas Service Company seeks a Geoscience Country Manager to come on board.
The successful applicant will:
- Set strategic and tactical direction for a country or area regarding policy/procedures
- Contribute toward work force staffing, and budgeting of assigned personnel within engineering disciplines in the Geoscience and Reservoir Formation departments.
Managerial responsibilities also include establishing and maintaining the technical standards within the discipline and the development of competence of employees falling within incumbent's given area or country.
Employees in this position participate in decisions regarding the acquisition and execution of contracts.
The successful applicant may supervise several subordinate supervisors or team leaders.
Requirements for this role:
- B.Sc. or M.Sc. in Science, Technology, Engineering, or Mathematics
- Minimum of 10 years of previous experience to include managerial experience
- Experience working in a managerial function for a leading Service Company
- Strong background in Geoscience, Reservoir Evaluation & Formation
For more information about this role please contact our London office
